gister of fleet driver trainers when you go for your check test.</p>\n\n<h2>How the test works</h2>\n\n<p>Check tests are based on the examiner observing a normal lesson which should last for around 1 hour. After the lesson you should allow at least 15 minutes for the debrief.</p>\n\n<p>There are 3 possible ways for your fleet check to be carried out.</p>\n\n<h3>Option 1 - a customer you haven&rsquo;t assessed</h3>\n\n<p>You can bring a customer who you haven&rsquo;t assessed and give an occupational risk presentation to them, and then introduce them to the training vehicle, covering the safety checks. You&rsquo;d have to do a driver assessment and profile to establish their main risk areas and provide the necessary coaching.</p>\n\n<h3>Option 2 - a customer you&rsquo;ve assessed</h3>\n\n<p>You can bring a customer you&rsquo;ve already assessed. You&rsquo;ll need to tell the examiner what main risk areas you intend to provide coaching for and do that during the check test.</p>\n\n<h3>Option 3 - a role-play check test</h3>\n\n<p>You can have a have a role-play check test. The examiner will play the role of the customer and simulate important risk faults for you to identify, analyse and coach on. </p>\n\n<h2>Your check test result</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll get a <a href=\"/adi-check-test-what-to-expect/your-check-test-grade\" title=\"Your check test grade\">grade at the end of your check test</a>. This works the same as a normal ADI check test.</p>\n\n<h2>Being removed from the register</h2>\n\n<p>You can end up being removed from both the ADI register and the register of fleet drivers if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>don’t pass the fleet driver check test</li>\n  <li>don’t attend your fleet driver check test</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/become-a-fleet-driver-trainer/fleet-driver-trainer-fees","slug":"fleet-driver-trainer-fees","order":10,"title":"Fleet driver trainer fees","body":"<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Fee type</th>\n      <th>Cost</th>\n 