on-the-register\" title=\"Claim compensation\">claim compensation</a> if you&rsquo;ve been suspended but are not then taken off the register.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There are different <a href=\"http://www.dvtani.gov.uk/adi/adiregistration.asp\" title=\"Rules about your ADI registration\" rel=\"external\">rules for your <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> registration</a> in Northern Ireland.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-instructor-suspension-your-rights/when-you-can-be-suspended","slug":"when-you-can-be-suspended","order":2,"title":"When you can be suspended","body":"<p>Your approved driving instructor (<abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr>) registration can be suspended if the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> registrar thinks you pose a significant threat to public safety.</p>\n\n<p>For example, if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>have been convicted of a sexual or violent offence</li>\n  <li>are giving dangerous instruction that&rsquo;s a major risk to the safety of your pupils and other road users</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Telling you if you’re suspended</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll get a letter from the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> registrar to tell you that your registration is suspended.</p>\n\n<p>This will usually be at that same time that the registrar writes to tell you that they&rsquo;re considering taking you off the register. </p>\n\n<h2>Challenging your suspension</h2>\n\n<p>You can use a judicial review to challenge the way in which the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> registrar made the decision to suspend you. </p>\n\n<p>The review only looks at whether the right procedures have been followed, rather than the decision itself.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n461-eng.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Judicial review claim form' (PDF, 416KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Judicial review claim form’ (PDF, 416KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n461-notes-eng.pdf\" title=\"Guidance notes on completing the judicial review claim form' (PDF, 222KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guidance notes on completing the judicial review claim form’ (PDF, 222KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You still have the right to <a href=\"/appeal-driving-instructor-registration-decision\" title=\"Appeal against the ADI registrar's decision\">appeal against the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> registrar’s decision</a> to remove you if you end up being taken off the register.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-instructor-suspension-your-rights/compensation-if-you-stay-on-the-register","slug":"compensation-if-you-stay-on-the-register","order":3,"title":"Compensation if you stay on the register","body":"<p>You can get compensation if your approved driving instructor (<abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr>) registration was suspended, but you weren&rsquo;t taken off the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> register.</p>\n\n<p>This includes cases where:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you win an appeal against the decision to take you off the register</li>\n  <li>the registrar considers taking you off the register, but then ends the suspension and lets you stay on the register</li>\n  <li>the registrar hasn’t made a decision about taking you off the register within 75 days</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>What you can claim</h2>\n\n<p>You can claim compensation for income and non-income losses as a result of being suspended.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can also claim for the cost of preparing your compensation application.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Income losses</h3>\n\n<p>‘Income losses’ are what you’d have got from giving driving lessons during the time you were suspended.</p>\n\n<h3>Non-income losses</h3>\n\n<p>‘Non-income losses’ are other losses you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>can give a monetary value to</li>\n  <li>incurred (within reason) while you were suspended</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Examples of non-income losses include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>any reasonable costs you needed to pay to prepare your compensation application</li>\n  <li>the interest on a loan you had to take out as a result of the suspension</li>\n  <li>the value of any damage that the suspension caused to your driving school business if you run one</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-instructor-suspension-your-rights/how-to-claim-compensation","slug":"how-to-claim-compensation","order":4,"title":"How to claim compensation","body":"<p>Download the application form and send it, with evidence to support your claim, to the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>).</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/dsa-bl/dsa-adi-compensation-application.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Application for payment of compensation' form (PDF, 21KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for payment of compensation’ form (PDF, 21KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br />Approved Driving Instructor Registrar\n<br />Driving Standards Agency\n<br />The Axis Building\n<br />112 Upper Parliament Street\n<br />Nottingham\n<br />NG1 6LP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>When to claim</h2>\n\n<p>You must send your claim within 2 years of whichever of these dates is later:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the date your suspension ended</li>\n  <li>the date you were told you’d won your appeal against the approved driving instructor (<abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr>) registrar</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can claim outside of the 2 years in special situations.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who can make the claim</h2>\n\n<p>You, as the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> who was suspended, must sign the declaration with the application form.</p>\n\n<p>You’re only allowed to sign the declaration on behalf of someone in limited situations, eg where the <abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr> has died and you’re allowed to represent them.</p>\n\n<h2>Evidence to support your claim</h2>\n\n<p>You should send documents that prove the basis of your claim, eg showing why you&rsquo;ve based your claim for income losses on a certain hourly rate.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll need to consider which documents will help <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> decide that you&rsquo;ve sent a valid claim, eg bank statements, payslips or a loan agreement.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-instructor-suspension-your-rights/working-out-your-losses","slug":"working-out-your-losses","order":5,"title":"Working out your losses","body":"<p>You’ll need to work out your income and non-income losses to send your claim.</p>\n\n<h2>Work out your income losses</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll need to work how much you’d have reasonably expected to earn during the time you were suspended.</p>\n\n<p>This should be based on your income for a period that you can directly compare with, eg the same period the previous year. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You should base your claim on the period that best compares to the time you were suspended if you can’t directly compare with a previous year.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If your claim is for a different amount to what’s shown in the previous period, you should explain why, eg a major change in how many pupils you taught in the weeks just before you were suspended.</p>\n\n<h2>Work out your non-income losses</h2>\n\n<p>Your claim will need to make clear:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>how the non-income losses were incurred</li>\n  <li>why they are reasonable costs</li>\n  <li>how you have worked them out</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You’ll need to send documents that clearly support your claim.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can claim for the value of any damage that the suspension caused to your driving school business if you run one.</p>\n\n<p>You can claim for the interest paid on a loan that you took out because your income stopped from being suspended.</p>\n\n<h2>Help working out your non-income losses</h2>\n\n<p>You can claim for the cost of preparing your compensation application. This can include the cost of getting expert help to work out how much your non-income losses are.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You’ll need to prove that the cost was reasonable, eg by showing that you didn’t pay a higher fee than usually applies.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-instructor-suspension-your-rights/the-decision-on-your-compensation-claim","slug":"the-decision-on-your-compensation-claim","order":6,"title":"The decision on your compensation claim","body":"<p>You’ll get a letter from the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>) within 28 days to either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>tell you you&rsquo;re being paid the amount you claimed for or a different amount</li>\n  <li>ask for more information to prove your claim</li>\n  <li>ask permission to go to a third party to prove your claim</li>\n  <li>tell you the claim hasn&rsquo;t been allowed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When you’ll get your payment</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll get the payment within 45 days of <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> telling you that you&rsquo;re going to be paid.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You must give any new information you find that’s relevant to your claim within 6 years of getting your compensation. You must do this within 1 month of finding it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Interim payments</h2>\n\n<p>You can get an interim payment:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>if you&rsquo;re in special situations, eg significant financial hardship</li>\n  <li>for part of the claim if it can be easily and quickly checked</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>If more information is needed</h2>\n\n<p>You must send any extra information <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> needs within 28 days. This can be extended in special situations.</p>\n\n<p>You must sign a statement to say the information is true to the best of your knowledge when you send it.</p>\n\n<h2>Not giving more information</h2>\n\n<p>You should tell <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> in writing if you cannot give the extra information, and the reason why. <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will do whatever it can to process the claim if this happens.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Your claim can be delayed if the extra information is not available, or you don’t give it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The part of the claim that needs the extra information can be rejected.</p>\n\n<h2>After you’re asked for more information</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will write to you within 28 days of either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>getting the extra information</li>\n  <li>the deadline for giving the extra information running out</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The letter from <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>tell you you&rsquo;re being paid the amount you claimed for or a different amount</li>\n  <li>ask for more information to prove your claim</li>\n  <li>tell you the claim hasn&rsquo;t been allowed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Appeal against the decision</h2>\n\n<p>You can <a href=\"/appeal-driving-instructor-registration-decision\" title=\"Appeal to the transport tribunal\">appeal to the transport tribunal</a> if you disagree with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the decision that you can&rsquo;t get compensation</li>\n  <li>the amount of compensation you’re going to get</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice 