join-the-register","slug":"ways-to-join-the-register","order":2,"title":"Ways to join the register","body":"<p>There are 2 ways to join the register of post-test motorcycle trainers (<abbr title=\"Register of post-test motorcycle trainers\">RPMT</abbr>):</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>pass 3 qualifying tests</li>\n  <li>pass a theory test and complete a training course</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Option 1 - pass 3 qualifying tests</h2>\n\n<p>In this option you have to:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>Apply to join the register.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Pass a theory test.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Pass a practical test to prove your ability to ride.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Pass a practical test to prove your ability to instruct.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You don’t have to take the riding ability test if you’ve passed the <a href=\"/dsa-special-tests-for-instructors\" title=\"Driving Standards Agency (DSA) special test\">Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>) special test</a> with an ‘A’ or ‘B’ grade within the last 2 years.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You’re allowed 3 attempts at the riding ability and instructional ability tests. You have to take the theory test again if you fail. You have to wait 2 years from when you first passed the theory test before you can take it again.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must pass the final test within 2 years of passing the theory test.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Option 2 - pass a theory test and complete a training course</h2>\n\n<p>In this option you have to:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>Apply to join the register.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Pass a theory test.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Complete a <a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/dsa/rpmt-trainer\" title=\"Training courses accredited by DSA\" rel=\"external\">training course accredited by <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>.</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must do the training course within 2 years of passing the theory test. You have to start the process again if you don’t.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/register-post-test-motorcycle-trainers-rpmt/apply-to-join-the-register","slug":"apply-to-join-the-register","order":3,"title":"Apply to join the register","body":"<p>To apply to join the register of post-test motorcycle trainers (<abbr title=\"Register of post-test motorcycle trainers\">RPMT</abbr>), download the application form and send it to the Driving Standards Agency.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/dsa-bl/dsa-rpmt-application-form.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘Application to join the register of post-test motorcycle trainers’ form (PDF, 343KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application to join the <abbr title=\"Register of post-test motorcycle trainers\">RPMT</abbr>’ form (PDF, 343KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br /><abbr title=\"Register of post-test motorcycle trainers\">RPMT</abbr>\n<br />Driving Standards Agency\n<br />The Axis Building\n<br />112 Upper Parliament Street\n<br />Nottingham\n<br />NG1 6LP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/register-post-test-motorcycle-trainers-rpmt/taking-the-theory-test","slug":"taking-the-theory-test","order":4,"title":"Taking the theory test","body":"<p>You can <a href=\"/book-your-instructor-theory-test\" title=\"Book your instructor theory test\">book your instructor theory test</a> when the Driving Standards Agency has accepted your application to join the register.</p>\n\n<h2>Documents to take to your test</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring both parts of your driving licence - the photocard and the paper counterpart. You must take your signed driving licence and a valid passport if you have an old-style paper licence.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Your test won’t go ahead and you’ll have to pay again if you don’t bring the right documents.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Multiple-choice questions</h2>\n\n<p>You’re allowed up to 90 minutes for the multiple-choice part of the test.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll be asked 100 questions in total. There are 25 questions in 4 categories. To pass the multiple-choice part you must get both:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>an overall score of at least 85 out of 100</li>\n  <li>at least 20 out of 25 in each of the 4 categories</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You will fail if you get an overall mark of 85 or higher, but don’t score high enough in each category.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Hazard perception</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then be shown 14 clips that feature every day road scenes. There will be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>one developing hazard in 13 clips</li>\n  <li>2 developing hazards in one clip</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>A developing hazard is something that may cause you to take some action, such as changing speed or direction.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can get up to 5 points for each clip.  The earlier you notice a developing hazard and make a response, the higher you score. You need to score at least 57 points out of 75 to pass this part.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/register-post-test-motorcycle-trainers-rpmt/taking-the-riding-ability-test","slug":"taking-the-riding-ability-test","order":5,"title":"Taking the riding ability test","body":"<p>To book your riding ability test, use the application form that the Driving Standards Agency sends to you when you&rsquo;ve passed the theory test.</p>\n\n<p>The test lasts around 1 hour.</p>\n\n<h2>What to bring to your test</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your valid Great Britain or Northern Ireland driving licence</li>\n  <li>a suitable motorcycle</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You need to bring both parts of your driving licence - the photocard and the paper counterpart.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You must take your signed driving licence and a valid passport if you have an old-style paper licence.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Your test won’t go ahead and you’ll lose your fee if you don’t bring the right documents and a suitable motorcycle.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Rules for the motorcycle you use</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring a suitable category A motorcycle for the test. It must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>be properly taxed and insured</li>\n  <li>be roadworthy and meet all legal requirements</li>\n  <li>have a power output of at least 35kW</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It must not display ‘L’ plates.</p>\n\n<h2>The eyesight test</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll have to read a number plate from a distance of:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>27 metres for vehicles with a new-style number plate</li>\n  <li>27.5 metres for vehicles with an old-style number plate</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>New-style number plates start with 2 letters followed by 2 numbers, eg AB51 ABC.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must use glasses or contact lenses during the whole test if you need them to read the number plate.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You’ll fail the test if you don’t pass the eyesight test.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Riding ability</h2>\n\n<p>Before you start the main part of the test you&rsquo;ll have to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>answer 5 vehicle safety questions</li>\n  <li>wheel your motorcycle and use a stand</li>\n  <li>do an emergency stop, a ‘U’  turn or a slow ride</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>When the main part of the test starts, the examiner will give you instruction over a radio. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’ll ride in varying road and traffic conditions, including motorways or dual carriageways where possible.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll have to prove your ability to ride safely and legally at all times during the test.</p>\n\n<h2>Your test result</h2>\n\n<p>The examiner will give you the result at the end of the test.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’ll pass the riding ability test if you make 6 riding faults or less.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll fail if you make a serious or dangerous fault, or make more than 6 riding faults.</p>\n\n<h3>Failing the first or second attempt</h3>\n\n<p>You can take the test again if you fail the test at either your first or second attempt.</p>\n\n<h3>Failing the third attempt</h3>\n\n<p>You have to retake and pass the <a href=\"taking-the-theory-test\" title=\"Taking the theory test\">theory test</a> again if you fail the riding ability test 3 times.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You have to wait 2 years from when you first passed the theory test before you can take it again.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/register-post-test-motorcycle-trainers-rpmt/taking-the-instructional-ability-test","slug":"taking-the-instructional-ability-test","order":6,"title":"Taking the instructional ability test","body":"<p>To book the instructional ability test, use the application form you&rsquo;re given when you pass the riding ability test.</p>\n\n<p>The test lasts around 1 hour.</p>\n\n<h2>What to bring to your test</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your valid Great Britain or Northern Ireland driving licence</li>\n  <li>a suitable motorcycle</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You need to bring both parts of your driving licence - the photocard and the paper counterpart.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You must take your signed driving licence and a valid passport if you have an old-style paper licence.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Your test won’t go ahead and you’ll lose your fee if you don’t bring the right documents and a suitable motorcycle.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Rules for the motorcycle you use</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring a suitable category A motorcycle for the test. It must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>be properly taxed and insured</li>\n  <li>be roadworthy and meet all legal requirements</li>\n  <li>have a power output of at least 35kW</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It must not display ‘L’ plates.</p>\n\n<h2>How the test works</h2>\n\n<p>The test has 2 parts and assesses your instructional ability. To do this, the examiner will play the role of 1 of the following types of trainee: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a newly qualified rider attending for further post test training</li>\n  <li>a rider upgrading their motorcycle and attending for development</li>\n  <li>a rider returning to motorcycling after a long break</li>\n  <li>a rider advised to get training after taking a riding assessment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You have to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>identify and prioritise areas of weakness in the trainee’s riding and give appropriate instruction</li>\n  <li>reduce the trainee’s areas of risk by using appropriate coaching methods</li>\n  <li>give a summary of the trainee’s performance at the end of the session, highlighting areas where they need more training or self-development</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Part 1</h3>\n\n<p>The examiner will ask you do 1 of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>give a short presentation designed to initially raise awareness of rider risks</li>\n  <li>involve the trainee in an interactive practical machine and pre-ride check session</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Part 2</h3>\n\n<p>The examiner will ask you to do 1 of the following scenarios:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>move away, control and slow riding</li>\n  <li>junctions and roundabouts</li>\n  <li>motorways and dual carriageways</li>\n  <li>corners and bends</li>\n  <li>positioning</li>\n  <li>other road users</li>\n  <li>use of speed</li>\n  <li>progress and hesitancy</li>\n  <li>overtaking and filtering</li>\n  <li>separation distance</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The examiner will asses you on how you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>assess the trainee’s riding</li>\n  <li>communicate with the trainee</li>\n  <li>give appropriate coaching and show methods that would reduce the faults and risks identified</li>\n  <li>communicate a final summary of the trainee’s riding</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Your test result</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll be told your result at the end of the test. </p>\n\n<h3>Passing the test</h3>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’ll get a letter if you pass. It will include a declaration that you must sign before you get a register of post-test motorcycle trainers registration certificate.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You should send this to the Driving Standards Agency with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the correct fee for how long you’re registering for</li>\n  <li>2 passport-style photos</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br /><abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> \n<br />PO Box 280 \n<br />Newcastle-Upon-Tyne \n<br />NE99 1FP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h3>Failing the test</h3>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll get a letter confirming your result if you fail the test. This can be used as the application form for your next attempt.</p>\n\n<h3>Failing the first or second attempt</h3>\n\n<p>You can take the test again if you fail the test at either your first or second attempt.</p>\n\n<h3>Failing the third attempt</h3>\n\n<p>You have to retake and pass the <a href=\"taking-the-theory-test\" title=\"Taking the theory test\">theory test</a> and <a href=\"taking-the-riding-ability-test\" title=\"Taking the riding ability test\">riding ability test</a> again if you fail the instructional ability test 3 times.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You have to wait 2 years from when you first passed the theory test before you can take it again.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/register-post-test-motorcycle-trainers-rpmt/managing-your-registration","slug":"managing-your-registration","order":7,"title":"Managing your registration","body":"<p>You must carry your post-test training certificate with you whenever you&rsquo;re giving training.</p>\n\n<h2>Renewing your registration</h2>\n\n<p>Your registration lasts for either 1 year or 4 years. </p>\n\n<p>You should apply to renew your registration at least 2 weeks before your current registration runs out. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You’re responsible for remembering when to renew your registration.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To renew, download the application form and send it to the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>) with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the correct fee for how long you&rsquo;re renewing for</li>\n  <li>2 passport-style photos</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Make cheques and postal orders payable to &lsquo;Driving Standards Agency&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/dsa-bl/dsa-rpmt-renewal-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Renewal of registration for the register of post-test motorcycle trainer registration' (PDF, 398KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Renewal of registration for the register of post-test motorcycle trainer registration’ (PDF, 398KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br /><abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>\n<br />PO Box 280\n<br />Newcastle-Upon-Tyne\n<br />NE99 1FP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>You can re-register using the same form within 12 months of your registration running out. You won&rsquo;t have to go through the qualifying process again.</p>\n\n<h2>Check tests and monitoring</h2>\n\n<p>You must take &lsquo;check tests&rsquo; with <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> to make sure that you keep up the standards needed to be on the register. </p>\n\n<p>You must take a check test within the first year of joining the register. <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will contact you to arrange this.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll get a grading of either &lsquo;satisfactory&rsquo; or &lsquo;unsatisfactory&rsquo; at each check test.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can 