ee licence</h2>\n\n<p>You should return your trainee licence to <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> if you aren’t using it, eg because of a long period of illness.</p>\n\n<p>You won&rsquo;t get a refund, but <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will know that you haven’t had full use of the licence. This will be a factor in deciding whether to give you another licence in future.</p>\n\n<h2>Lost or stolen licence</h2>\n\n<p>You should <a href=\"/contact-police\" title=\"Tell the police\">tell the police</a> straight away if your licence is lost or stolen. They will give you a crime reference number.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You’ll have to pay £3 if you lose your licence or can’t give <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> a crime reference number.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To get a replacement, you&rsquo;ll need to send the following to <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the crime reference number</li>\n  <li>a recent passport-style photograph if you don&rsquo;t give <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> permission to use your photocard driving licence photo or don&rsquo;t have a photocard licence</li>\n  <li>the fee if your licence was lost or you can&rsquo;t give a crime reference number</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n \n\n<br />Approved Driving Instructor Registrar\n<br />Driving Standards Agency\n<br />The Axis Building\n<br />112 Upper Parliament Street\n<br />Nottingham\n<br />NG1 6LP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/trainee-driving-instructor-licence-the-rules/when-your-trainee-licence-runs-out","slug":"when-your-trainee-licence-runs-out","order":4,"title":"When your trainee licence runs out","body":"<p>Your trainee licence lasts for 6 months. When it runs out you must stop being paid for giving driving lessons.</p>\n\n<h2>Getting another licence</h2>\n\n<p>You can <a href=\"/apply-for-a-trainee-driving-instructor-licence\" title=\"Apply for a trainee licence\">apply for another trainee licence</a> if you feel you haven&rsquo;t had the full benefit out it. You&rsquo;ll need to pay the fee again.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can’t be paid for giving driving lessons when you don’t have a valid trainee licence.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;re more likely to get another licence if you told the Driving Standards Agency you had stopped using the first, eg because of a period of illness.</p>\n\n<p>It’s unlikely that you’ll get another licence just to give you more time to pass the approved driving instructor (<abbr title=\"Approved driving instructor\">ADI</abbr>) part 3 test.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong> </p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s unlikely you&rsquo;ll get another trainee licence if you already have a full-time job and you can only practise using your licence in the evenings and at weekends.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can <a href=\"/appeal-driving-instructor-registration-decision\" title=\"Appeal to the transport tribunal\">appeal to the transport tribunal</a> if you’re not given another licence.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:18:26+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Business Link","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/businesslink.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"short_description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=businesslink","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/businesslink"},"parent":null},{"title":"Teaching people to drive","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/driving%2Fteaching-people-to-drive.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Becoming an instructor, applying for licences, booking tests and rules","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=driving%2Fteaching-people-to-d